9
[h2 
	" Getting a page
	$LF
]h2
[p 
	"As a TASer on this site you can request a user page. Contact 
	(__wikiLink|Users|an administrator or admin assistant)
	", or simply send 
	(__wikiLink|user:adelikat)
	" a PM on the forums. On the page, you can write things about yourself, about your TAS projects, about your thoughts, and so on.
	$LF
]p
[p 
	"User pages differ from regular pages in these aspects:
	$LF
]p
[ul 
	[li 
		" User pages can be edited by their owner, even if they're not an editor.
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" User pages provide automatic links to the owner's forum profile, submissions etc.
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" User pages enable 
		[tt 
			"[user:name]
		]tt
		" links on the wiki, which lead to your user page.
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" User pages are denoted by a house icon on the 
		(__wikiLink|Recent Changes)
		" page.
		$LF
	]li
]ul
[h2 
	" Guidelines
	$LF
]h2
[p 
	"Do not use the user page as a notepad. Rendering and storing the pages requires expensive server resources.
	$LF
]p
[p 
	"You should read the 
	(__wikiLink|Text Formatting Rules)
	" to learn how to do add
	$LF
	"simple formatting to your text.
	$LF
]p
[p 
	"The administration reserves the discretion to delete user pages that do not follow these guidelines.
	$LF
]p
[h2 
	" Subpages
	$LF
]h2
[p 
	"Once you have a user page you can also create subpages within that namespace.
	$LF
	"For example, if your username is "
	(__wikiLink|user:Bisqwit)
	"", you can create a subpage "Projects" by editing the page "
	(__wikiLink|Bisqwit/Projects)
	"".
	$LF
]p
[p 
	"If your page is becoming too long, you should consider dividing it into subpages.
	$LF
	"Subpages are pages that consists of the main page name, a slash, and the subpage name. For example, Bisqwit's 
	(__wikiLink|Bisqwit/Projects|projects)
	" page is 
	[tt 
		"Bisqwit/Projects
	]tt
	". A subpage can also have subpages: 
	(__wikiLink|Bisqwit/Projects/ChronoCross)
	$LF
]p
[ul 
	[li 
		" To automatically list your subpages, insert this code onto your main page: 
		[tt 
			"[module:ListSubPages]
		]tt
		".
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" To automatically create a link back to the parent page, insert this code onto your sub page: 
		[tt 
			"[module:ListParents]
		]tt
		".
	]li
]ul
